results.name: Decimal expansion of the mean car density associated with Solomon's variation in Renyi's one-dimensional parking problem.
reference: Steven R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Cambridge University Press, 2003, Section 5.3 Renyi's parking constant, p. 279.
formula: integral_(x>=0) (2*x+1)*exp(-2*(x+exp(-x)-1)]*exp(-2*(-Ei(-x)+log(x)+gamma)) dx, where Ei is the exponential integral function and gamma the Euler-Mascheroni constant.
mathematica: digits = 102; NIntegrate[(2*x + 1)*Exp[-2*(x + Exp[-x] - 1)]*Exp[-2*(-ExpIntegralEi[-x] + Log[x] + EulerGamma)], {x, 0, Infinity}, WorkingPrecision -> digits + 5] // RealDigits[#, 10, digits] & // First
results.author: _Jean-François Alcover_, May 27 2014
